<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
When the author is anonymous, include the title of the work (shortened if necessary) and any 
relevant page number(s), in parentheses, immediately following the cited material.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (&#34;Study Smarter, Not Harder&#34; 10&#45;11).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the title of the work in your sentence, with the relevant page number(s) in parentheses.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&#34;Study Smarter, Not Harder&#34; suggests that &#34;the default position is markedly 
	affected&#34; (11).
</blockquote>
<br>
When the author is referred to more than once in the same paragraph only the page number is 
needed for subsequent citations, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (&#34;Study Smarter, Not Harder&#34; 10&#45;11). In addition 
	&hellip;was a common feature (11).
</blockquote>
